{"id":2305,"date":"2023-04-03T22:35:19","date_gmt":"2023-04-03T17:05:19","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost\/?page_id=2305"},"modified":"2023-11-06T23:21:37","modified_gmt":"2023-11-06T17:51:37","slug":"pa","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/localhost\/?page_id=2305","title":{"rendered":"Painting"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button has-custom-width wp-block-button__width-100 has-custom-font-size is-style-outline has-small-font-size\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background-color has-foreground-background-color has-text-color has-background has-link-color wp-element-button\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost\/\" style=\"border-radius:100px;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)\">Homepage<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Each brush type serves a specific purpose, allowing to achieve different effects and textures. For watercolor paintings, a soft and round brushes to achieve smooth washes and delicate details. Fabric boards provide a sturdy surface for the artwork, allowing to work with precision and control. To enhance the flow and transparency of my paints, a thinner, which helps to achieve the desired consistency. All the images here are downscaled to less than 1000-pixel height and width, to not slow down the site. Finer details might not be visible.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1000\" height=\"861\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/buddha.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2501\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/buddha.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/buddha-300x258.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/buddha-150x129.jpg 150w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/buddha-768x661.jpg 768w, http:\/\/loca